SIMPLE: bis
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bis
<hw>Bis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>bis</ets>
twice, for <ets>duis</ets>, fr. root of <ets>duo</ets> two. See
<er>Two</er>, and cf. <er>Bi-</er>.]</ety> <def>Twice; -- a word showing
that something is, or is to be, repeated; as a passage of music, or an
item in accounts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bis-</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bis-
<hw>Bis-</hw>, <pos>pref.</pos> <def>A form of <er>Bi-</er>, sometimes
used before <it>s</it>, <it>c</it>, or a vowel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bisa antelope</ent>⟦br⟧
